JobFullDesc:
“You Lead the Way. We’ve Got Your Back.
At American Express, we know that with the right backing, people and businesses have the power to progress in incredible ways.  Whether we’re supporting our customers’ financial confidence to move ahead, taking commerce to new heights, or encouraging people to explore the world, our colleagues are constantly redefining what’s possible - and we’re proud to back each other every step of the way. When you join #TeamAmex, you become part of a diverse community of over 60,000 colleagues, all with a common goal to deliver an exceptional customer experience every day.” 
Be part of the continuing transformation within the Business and Vendor Management (“BVM”) organization. You’ll join a team of creative, curious and passionate professionals whose mission is to become the leading source of vendor data and reporting for American Express Technologies.  
The successful individual ensures that our products meets the evolving needs of the enterprise through continuous innovation, evaluation and deployment. Requires strong organizational, technical and creative problem-solving skills. Requires strong multi-business unit stakeholder management. Must work well in a dynamic, complex environment and under deadline pressures. Coordinates the efforts of a scrum team or a set of scrum teams within a SAFe train to deploy the new features across markets and products. Brings new ideas to the table for future enhancements in BVM’s suit of insightful offerings.
The Product Manager has ultimate responsibility for decision making and prioritization for their backlog working with markets, compliance, marketing, design and engineering leaders to convert the product vision into a well-managed development roadmap.
Responsibilities:

Interacting with customers to identify needs and collaborative opportunities;
Brainstorming and negotiating effectively with various stakeholders to continuously define feature priority; 
Prioritizing engineering work and balancing the requirements of customers and stakeholders;
Enabling analytics-driven decision making to evolve products and usage;
Leading the product functional design, showcasing multiple design concepts or visual mockups, based on an intimate knowledge of the customer and technology;
Generating executive-level marketing material for product launches and product performance reporting;
Creating tailored communications based on varying customers and stakeholders;
Supporting build out of executive briefing content on key vendor relationships for the CIO office;
Maintaining marketing material templates for broader organizational use
Being a champion of the Agile mindset;
Driving product strategy, roadmap, and features;
Establishing the product’s goals and reviewing success metrics;
Managing the product life cycle from strategic planning to tactical execution;
Helping the team develop products by making difficult tradeoffs and removing roadblocks;
Prioritizing feature/story backlog;
Leading business feature breakdown into stories;
Writing and refining stories for scrum teams;
Tracks product performance post-launch to evaluate future investment;
Continuously improving products post-launch, prioritizing bugs and feature requests based on customer satisfaction;

 



5+ years’ experience in Product Management or Product Marketing with proven track record in defining winning product visions and roadmaps 
SAFe certified in either POPM, APM, or RTE
An established background in iterative development, Scaled Agile Framework and principles;
Must know how to write features and stories with proper acceptance criteria in Rally or Jira;
Enthusiasm for learning how complex systems and processes work, and how to make them better;
Ability to communicate product functionality;
Can balance technical knowledge and business acumen;
Experience with innovative and collaborative approaches to problem solving;
Ability to work well under pressure and adapts to changing priorities;
Ability to work with a strategic and big picture mindset;
Ability to learn quickly and work proactively with minimal direction;
Excellent communication skills with the ability to engage, influence, and inspire partners to drive collaboration and alignment;
High degree of organization, individual initiative and personal accountability;
BS/BA degree in related field  

Also Preferred

Understanding of Third-Party or Vendor Management 

“Employment eligibility to work with American Express in the U.S. is required as the company will not pursue visa sponsorship for these positions.” 
